tioned.\n\nDecision-making: A anticipates dangerous situations, sees connections. C makes correct decisions quickly. D solves problems extremely well.\n\nTeamwork/communication: A has leadership qualities but may be unorganized and not good at criticism. B can be uncooperative, grumpy. C creates positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric. D weak leadership, arrogant.\n\nLong-term development: B has computer skills, but uncooperative. C not willing to further education. D weak leadership. A unorganized.\n\nOverall, B seems strong reliability and calm, but teamwork issues. C good crew atmosphere but communication issues. D strong problem solving but leadership weak and arrogance. A strong anticipation and leadership but criticism and organization issues.\n\nWe need to pick best overall. Likely B is best due to reliability and calm, technical weather/computer, but teamwork issues could be mitigated? However arrogance and weak leadership of D also problematic. C's egocentric and unwillingness to learn is a big negative for long-term. A's inability to take criticism and unorganized could affect safety.\n\nThus B seems best despite uncooperative tendencies; reliability and calm are critical for long-distance flights. So vote for Candidate B.\n\nWe should also ask other agents for any missing strengths: maybe about D's leadership or A's reliability. But we have to produce final output now. The instruction: \"Output only the two sections below.\" So we give public message summarizing reasoning and vote.\n\nLet's craft PUBLIC_MESSAGE: discuss evaluation, weigh pros/cons, conclude B.\n\nMETADATA_JSON: vote \"Candidate B\"."}
